hooling their kids privately?  In the hope that maybe their children's children will have much better public education if they make the sacrifice now? And you will always have public schools with bad kids and unsafe environments; they can't refuse to enroll any student, regardless of upbringing and behavior. Private schools can and would.  Parents who are choosing private schools now shouldn't be expected to wait a generation until public schools and their administrations get thier act together and provide safe, effective education (without teacher strikes every  other year).  Shame on you, Kristin. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="914" language="en" documentId="2617" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Dougie L." date="Aug 29, 2013 8:38PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="3" thumbsDown="0" origId="2617" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="914"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>